casebody.data:
Robert KELLY v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary Annex, Fort Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 2279. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. May 9, 1941. Thomas Raber Taylor, of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Homer Davis, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Circuit Judge, and SYMES, District Judge,

PER CURIAM.

Appeal1 dismissed May 1, 1941, on appellee’s motion.
